WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.800
[Unknown]: I.V.M.

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:36.000
[Amit Varma]: The point Lipman made in that chapter was that all of us have a picture of the world in our heads

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:42.000
[Amit Varma]: and that picture can never correspond to the actual world exactly or even to other such pictures inside other people's heads

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:44.000
[Amit Varma]: because the world is too complicated.

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:52.000
[Amit Varma]: We are a storytelling species and all of us build or subscribe to simple narratives that help make sense of a complex world.

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:55.000
[Amit Varma]: This is the necessary mechanism and there's nothing wrong in this.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:01.000
[Amit Varma]: However, in modern times when our means of getting news and knowledge are widely dispersed

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:07.000
[Amit Varma]: and the political discourse is so polarized, it means that these narratives diverge furiously

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:13.000
[Amit Varma]: more than it used to in the past when the media was monolithic and there was some sort of broad consensus on the truth.

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:21.000
[Amit Varma]: And once we build a narrative in our heads about the world, we only accept news and information that conforms to this narrative.

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:28.000
[Amit Varma]: There is too much cognitive dissonance otherwise, too much hard work for us to do to keep modifying that picture in our heads.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
[Amit Varma]: At some level, this explains the attractiveness of fake news.

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
[Amit Varma]: Anything that reinforces our worldview is legit, everything else is fake.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:42.000
[Amit Varma]: You might think that this is fine, let people believe what they believe, but fake news has real consequences.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:48.000
[Amit Varma]: Rumors can kill people, decide elections, tear communities apart and spread cancer in our society

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:55.000
[Amit Varma]: and it has never been as much of a threat as it is today, enabled and turbocharged by technology.

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:57.000
[Amit Varma]: Something must be done.

